Phakaaathi has been led to believe that SuperSport United are allegedly interested in the services of Cape Town Spurs Abednego Mosiatlhaga, who is in his sixth season in the GladAfrica Championship after he had a taste of top-flight football with the now defunct Bidvest Wits. READ ALSO: Mbule set to snub Sundowns and join Chiefs? The capital city outfit are understood to be locked in talks for the 27-year-old, but Spurs are not keen to let go of one of their key players. “We have always indicated that we will sell our players if a good offer comes. Some teams have come knocking at our door, especially after he scored 18 goals a few seasons ago, but what was put on the table has never been satisfactory,” said a mole within the club.